#Text=Easily Increase Your Gas Mileage
#Text=Not everyone can go out and buy the latest hybrid model .
#Text=However , you can learn how to easily increase your gas mileage with your current car .
#Text=Driving well and taking good care of your vehicle are all it takes to go further on a tank of gas .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Drive the speed limit .
#Text=Experts estimate that you lose 20 cents for every you go over the highway speed limit .
#Text=Use your vehicle 's cruise control for highway driving .
#Text=The cruise control keeps the accelerator even and prevents sudden surges from stepping on the gas .
#Text=Cruise control wo n't work in favor of your gas mileage if you live in a mountainous area , as the accelerator will be constantly surging going up frequent steep hills .
#Text=Shut the car off if you 'll be idling for longer than 15-30 seconds .
#Text=Drive moderately and do n't rev the engine .
#Text=Anticipate having to stop and slow down way ahead of traffic .
#Text=Change your oil regularly and rotate or replace your tires when needed .
#Text=A dirty air filter or worn-out spark plugs can also seriously drain your gas mileage and should be fixed or replaced .
#Text=Use the motor oil recommended in your vehicle owner 's manual .
#Text=Motor oil additives can also make a difference .
#Text=Look for an oil in your car 's recommended grade that advertises energy conservation or uses the API performance logo .
#Text=Check your vehicle owner 's manual to see what octane of fuel is recommended for your vehicle ; for most cars , regular octane is ideal .
#Text=Reduce engine speed by using the highest gear available .
#Text=Not only will this easily increase your gas mileage , it will also reduce the wear and tear on your engine .
#Text=Do n't use a gear that is too high .
#Text=Take luggage and racks off the exterior of your car when you 're not using them .
#Text=Anything extra on the outside of your vehicle increases drag .
#Text=Remove unnecessary junk from your trunk , as extra pounds will weigh a car down .
#Text=It 's estimated that for every 250 pounds hauled , you lose per gallon .
#Text=Travel when you know traffic will be lighter , if possible .
#Text=Combine trips to run several errands at once in certain areas of town .
#Text=Try not to use your four-wheel drive if possible .
#Text=The drive components increase fuel consumption .
#Text=Keep your tires inflated at optimum levels .
#Text=Not only is this good for the wear of your car and safety , you may be able to get a modest increase in gas mileage .
#Text=Tips
#Text=On the highway , always keep your revs below 3000rpm , this will reduce the amount of gas being used to move the vehicle .
#Text=Keep track of your fuel savings by saving receipts and calculating your fuel economy over distances traveled .
#Text=Make notes about which gas mileage saving methods you tried and their result .
#Text=Avoid any fuel additives that claim it can easily increase your gas mileage .
#Text=The Federal Trade Commission warns that any savings from these products will be minimal .
#Text=Rolling down the windows and forgoing air conditioning made no difference in tests of gas consumption .
